<article>
    <h1>Boo&#xAD;tle&#x2019;s</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210103/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-03"><time>2021-01-03</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Where: 733 Have­lock Road; open: 7.30am to 7.30pm daily Info: Call 9875-2091 or go to www.face­book.com/Boo­tles. mar­ket</p>
    <p>Not­ing the wide gap i n prices be­tween main­stream su­per­mar­ket chains and niche bou­tique gro­cers, Mr Ben Scott, co-founder of Boo­tle’s store in Tiong Bahru, is look­ing to shake things up by be­ing the mid­dle ground that pro­vides qual­ity pro­duce at rea­son­able prices.</p>
    <p>The Bri­ton, who comes from a fam­ily of farm­ers and has lived in Sin­ga­pore for 15 years, says: “I find it frus­trat­ing to pay of­ten more than twice for pro­duce here than I do in the United States, United King­dom or Aus­tralia – es­pe­cially when com­par­ing pro­duce that is im­ported there too and has trav­elled the same dis­tance.</p>
    <p>“I wanted to cre­ate some­thing pos­i­tive for Sin­ga­pore – like a farmer’s mar­ket of­fer­ing high stan­dards and ser­vice at prices that mid­dle-class Sin­ga­pore­ans can af­ford.”</p>
    <p>Boo­tle’s opened in Oc­to­ber last year, with a re­tail sec­tion that has ex­panded across three shop­houses. It houses a butch­ery, a fish­mon­ger and kitchens to pre­pare take­away meals.</p>
    <p>Friendly staff – mostly with culi­nary train­ing – are on hand to guide you through the premises and dish out ad­vice on how best to cook the pro­duce.</p>
    <p>The pro­duce is clearly la­belled – chem­i­cal-free, or­ganic or con­ven­tional (uses syn­thetic fer­tilis­ers and pes­ti­cides) – for cus­tomers to make more in­formed choices.</p>
    <p>You can get chilled free-range chicken wings (from $7.20 for 400g) from Aus­tralia, frozen monk­fish medal­lions ($18 for 220g) from Bri­tain, and beef­steak toma­toes ($4.90 for a 400g pack) from Cameron High­lands.</p>
    <p>Items for the pantry in­clude ve­gan cul­tured but­ter ($14), lemon dill macadamia cheese ($18) and porcini mush­room milk choco­late ($6).</p>

